# train data
data = read.csv('../data/train.csv')
data = data[-1]
x = data$Cover_Type
for (i in 1:(length(data)-1)) {
  boxplot(data[, i] ~ x, xlab=colnames(data)[i])
}

# independence test, Chi-squared test
library(MASS)
for (i in 1:(length(data) - 1)) {
  if (sd(data[, i]) != 0) {
    print(colnames(data)[i])
    tbl = table(data[, i], x)
    print(chisq.test(tbl))
  }
}
